        <h3 class="govuk-heading-l">How do I add a service to my account?</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            To add a service to your account you need to be an approver.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you have approver status, follow these few steps to add a service to your account.
        </p>
        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Go to 'services'.</li>
            <li>Choose 'add services to my account' from the related actions list on the right.</li>
            <li>Select the service you want and press the continue button.</li>
            <li>Select the forms or roles you require and press continue.</li>
            <li>The service will now be visible on the services dashboard, ready to use.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What if I need the service for multiple organisations?</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you have more than one organisation associated with your account, you will be prompted to select 
            which organisation you want to add a service to before you continue.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have to add the service for each organisation, one at a time.
        </p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Can I add a service as an end user?</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            No, you will need to request the service.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You can learn more about requesting access to a service in our easy to follow guide.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            <a class="govuk-link-bold" href="/services/request-access">How to request access to a service</a>
        </p>

